node.text:
@Mayalikes breathed life into her Sausalito rental home by embracing a mixture of textures, color, and styles, which was primarily inspired by a trip to Mexico City. “I am half Mexican and I wanted to draw inspiration from my roots. I love the natural materials, rich-hued colors, and textures found in Mexican design, but I wanted to tone down the vibrant colors with more neutrals and mix in some modern and mid-century modern design pieces,” Maya explains. Get a full tour of her warm, earthy space, and see how she beautifully handled the home’s “funky layout” at the link in our bio. 

(Image & Home: @mayalikes)
